original: Bohman, Bror Axel Emanuel, kon–sul, Oskarshamn, f. 26/2/97 i Virse-rum, Kalm. 1., av fabr. August B. o. h. h. — Realsk., hand isk., uti istud. Res. i Eur. o. Nord- o. Sydamer. Chef f. o. inneh. av A-B Bohmans Fanér-fabr. i Oskarshamn fr. 30, A-B Nord. Fanérfabr. i Vimmerby sed. 42. Styri-led, i A-B Sv. Handibank. platsstyr.
translated: Bohman, Bror Axel Emanuel, consul, Oskarshamn, b. 26/2/97 in Virserum, Kalm. 1., son of factory owner August B. and his wife. He attended high school and business school, and traveled in Europe, North and South America. He was the CEO and owner of A-B Bohmans Veneer factory in Oskarshamn from 1930, and A-B Nord. Veneer factory in Vimmerby from 1942. He was a board member in A-B Swed. Handibank and local manager. He married but the abbreviation for the year is not provided.

structured.name: Bror Axel Emanuel Bohman
structured.description: Swedish consul and CEO in the veneer industry
